text: So, Paige receives a wrestling biopic film before Hulk Hogan, Bret Hart, Andre the Giant, Ultimate Warrior, Brian Pillman, Ric Flair, the McMahon Family, Chris Benoit (Which was supposed to happen), Stone Cold Steve Austin, and Eddie Guerrero? Okay then. Judging from inaccurate flaws such as the WWE logo, which wasn't used until August 2014. Paige signed a developmental deal with WWE/FCW in 2011 when the scratch logo was still being used, the performance center existing at the start (which opened in 2013), and the fact they're calling her "Paige" instantly as if it's her real name tells me this won't be great at all. Besides, there's a documentary about Paige's introduction to WWE available on YouTube already. So, watching seems like it would be a waste of time. If you want a great wrestling based film that tells and showcases the life of a wrestler pretty authentically. Then I'd recommend "The Wrestler" (2008) with Mickey O'Rourke. It's a top notch quality film that this laughable movie could ever hope to reach.
